Hello,This is my first post to the group. My name is Ursula, and I am a =
Chicago-based writer who has written a number of books on Chicago&#39;s superna=
tural history and folklore. I just started a regular program of ITC experim=
entation a week ago today, after receiving several books from Mark Macy aft=
er he spoke at our Chicago Ghost Conference in October. Macy immediately st=
ruck me as an intensely sincere, peaceful person, and I wanted some of what=
 made him that way. I soon found out that his demeanor flows from his conne=
ction to and knowledge of the other side, which he has garnered through ITC=
. With Mark&#39;s advice to guide me, I put together a very simple setup and be=
gan recording for about ten minutes each morning at eleven. I got my first =
voice on Wednesday and, though it was a bit chilling, I was and am fascinat=
ed. This was a huge step for me because, like a lot of &quot;ghost hunters&quot; I wa=
s fascinated by voice phenomena but never wanted it in my own house! Previo=
usly, the thought of recording in my own home was terrifying, but now that =
I understand the bridge-building idea of ITC (as a separate thing from reco=
rding EVP at haunted sites)it&#39;s actually bringing me a lot of peace and foc=
us.My husband and I operate Chicago Hauntings tours, and we started our com=
pany in part to try to &quot;un-haunt&quot; some of the tragic sites in the city. We =
feel that by taking guests to the locations to tell the often covered-up st=
ories of the dead there we can help send on some of the negative energies/e=
ntities. ITC seems to really speak to this idea, in the way that it helps u=
s all grow spiritually BEFORE we pass over, so that we don&#39;t get &quot;left behi=
nd&quot; here when it&#39;s time to transition.Anyway, those are some of the inital =
feelings and thoughts I have as I start this program. I am eager to pick up=
 feelings, thoughts (and tips) from other experimenters. Thanks again for h=
aving me! 






